<br>
Evil. Some people wonder why I reguard people as Evil, and Neutral/Good, or Lightbringer. I don't have time to pick you out, those that are Neutral, and those that are good, and I really dont care.<br>
<br>
So I'll just call you, Neutral/Goods, Lightbringers, because I feel like it, and its what I've always called you. Don't like it?Tough. Thats what you get for not being evil.<br>
<br>
To truely be seen in the eyes of evil, their are some requirements that one must pass. This is to toss away lightbringers who will pretend to be evil just go gain our company or share a bed with some Random Tier'dal female.<br>
<br>
These requirements are simple and clear cut. You either are or you are not. Don't bitch and whine if you are not evil, accept it you bastard, and die.<br>
<br>
Evilness requires a bit of Religion.<br>
<br>
Our faith in dark paths is what firstly defines us as evil beings, however it is not the only thing that is required, however it is the second most powerful tell tale of an truely evil person.<br>
<br>
Cazic Thule<br>
Innoruuk<br>
Bertox<br>
Rallos Zek<br>
<br>
These are the four evil gods. No other gods are evil. Soluseck Ro is not evil. Why is he not evil? Simple, Fire burns for all. It may burn in the Rage of the Evil heart, but it also burns in the resolve of those that defend life.<br>
<br>
If you do not follow these four paths, you are NOT evil reguardless of what worthless race you are. I could care less if you are a Tier'dal Rogue of Bristlebane. You're not evil, and in the end of Norrath, you'll die with the rest of the Non believers.<br>
<br>
Why? Why does an Dark Elven Enchanter choose to follow no god? Because he is afraid to follow a God like Innoruuk, because some Humans in Qeynos or the Highelves in Felwithe might hate him. Its that simple. Get over it. If you want to swear loyality to a dark Lord, you will have to offer him your life, and all of your levels of power, and be reborn with his blessing. That is the only way for you.<br>
<br>
Its not about following a God.<br>
I say it here. I don't give my life for Innoruuk. I have no love for that diety. However.<br>
Each of these Dark Lords represents a path in a Dark Man or Woman's life.<br>
<br>
Fear.<br>
Hate.<br>
War.<br>
Death.<br>
<br>
These 4 things make up the Circle of Death. The Anti Circle of Life, where as the FEAR of your Opponets builds into their HATEred for you, which causes them to raise their arms and go to WAR against you, and you fighting and tearing their weak lightbringing arses apart, causing their DEATH. If you do not stand in this Circle of Death, then you are not evil.<br>
<br>
Race<br>
<br>
Woodelves, Highelves, Dwarves, Halflings, Vah Shir, and Barbarians have no capasity to be truely evil, no matter what god they follow. Woodelves and Highelves are the Children of Tunare. Evil Woodelves and Highelves would rather kill themselves then live their lives out as Woodelves and Highelves.<br>
The rest are the same. No true evil person would want to live as one of these worthless races. A True Hearted evil person would rather die then live their life as one of them.<br>
So they would kill themselves, and hope one of the 4 evil gods sees their evilness in their sprits, and be reborn as a more.. Suitable race.<br>
<br>
Class<br>
<br>
Just like Race, True hearted evil people would never live lives out as Druids, Rangers, or Paladins. They would rather die then do such, and they do. If they are truely evil, they will be reborn in the Image of one of the Dark Lords.<br>
<br>
The race and class of the evil person is truely important. Some however are under the misconception that you have to be Tier'dal to be an evil Enchanter, Evil Mage, or an Evil Wizard.<br>
<br>
Its a known fact that Human Mages can follow Bertox, Human Wizards can be followers of Innoruuk, and Enchanters.. I know Human Enchanters can follow Dark Gods.<br>
You'd be suprized about who can follow what.<br>
<br>
And this is the final, but it is the overriding requirement for anyone that claims to be a Truely evil person.<br>
<br>
This requirement is more important then any of the above.<br>
And its about Friendship, Loyality, and Helping.<br>
<br>
Contrary to Popular belief, Evil Helps Evil attain Evil goals. Its not an requirement.. Well it is, if you wish for Evil to become powerful. However, its not a requirement for one to be evil.<br>
<br>
Evil that helps the lightbringers is not evil at all. Helping a lightbringer brings their light into you, and evil you are not. A lightbringer you have become.<br>
<br>
How do you 'Help' Lightbringers?<br>
<br>
Every time you group with a Lightbringer, you help them.<br>
If you are in a Guild with lightbringers, you help them.<br>
If you are friends with a lightbringer, you help them.<br>
If you raid with a lightbringer, you help them.<br>
If you let a lightbringer join your raid, you help them.<br>
<br>
Their are ways to be redeemed however from this.<br>
That is throught death, execpt for when it Involves one Guilding with Lightbringers.<br>
<br>
If you are in a Guild of Lightbringers, leave them coldly, and then you may be able to reclaim your evilness.<br>
The rest of them, you must kill 'a Lightbringer'. The Lightbringer you helped, you slay. <br>
Thats the only way to redeem yourself from this, is that way. You don't kill him, get used to being a damned Lightbringer, bastard.<br>
<br>
That is all, for now. <p><P ALIGN=CENTER>
