Look, I know I'm no better; I mean, look at me, I'm here too.  The problem is that good and evil is something we mortals want desperately to be able to hold up and show off.  We want to be able to say &quot;Look at what I've done - I'm a good girl!&quot;  Or, &quot;Look at what I've done, I'm a bad boy!&quot;  Or, of course, &quot;Look at me, I'm upholding the balance!&quot;<br>
<br>
But it's not.  Good and evil are just personal concepts.  You think you're evil because you're a killer.  Well, do you kill dark elves?  If you're killing your people's enemies, that makes you a good guy... to your people, at least.  How can it be evil to just do your job?  I know of paladins who ruthlessly slaughter anyone they meet... obviously an evil thing... except for the fact that they're behind enemy lines.<br>
<br>
Look, I'm not saying you're not evil, and you're right, you're a very bad man, and shame on you.  But the fact that you feel it's necessary to point out the &quot;Rules&quot; of being evil just makes me feel that you're trying too hard to prove something to yourself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/4/02 12:09:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What it takes to be A True Hearted Evil Bastard</span><hr size=1> Heeeey.... I said a joke that DOESN'T worship Rodcet Nife!<br>
